Package: rsahmi
Title: Single-Cell Analysis of Host-Microbiome Interactions
Version: 0.0.2.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Yun", "Peng", , "yunyunp96@163.com", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-2801-3332"))
Description: A computational resource designed to accurately detect microbial
    nucleic acids while filtering out contaminants and false-positive taxonomic
    assignments from standard transcriptomic sequencing of mammalian tissues.
    For more details, see Ghaddar (2023) <doi:10.1038/s43588-023-00507-1>. This
    implementation leverages rust for fast and systematic microbial signal
    recovery and denoising from host tissue genomic sequencing.
Depends: 
    R (>= 4.2)
Imports: 
    blit (>= 0.1.0),
    mirai,
    cli,
    rlang,
    ggplot2,
    ShortRead,
    utils
Suggests:
    polars (>= 0.17.0)
